### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 25](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 25:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 25:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#001.md), Samuel dies; [Sa1
25:2](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#002.md), David in Paran sends to Nabal;
[Sa1 25:10](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#010.md), Provoked by Nabal's
churlishness, he minds to destroy him; [Sa1
25:14](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#014.md), Abigail understanding thereof,
[Sa1 25:18](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#018.md), takes a present; [Sa1
25:23](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#023.md), and by her wisdom, [Sa1
25:32](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#032.md), pacifies David; [Sa1
25:36](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#036.md), Nabal hearing thereof, dies;
[Sa1 25:39](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#039.md), David takes Abigail and
Ahinoam to be his wives; [Sa1 25:44](../../../bib/kjv/sa1025.htm#044.md),
Michal is given to Phalti.

